  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0b9c\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd 39 \u0b86\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd :  \u0b95\u0ba9\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9f\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bcb \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b9f\u00a0 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "39th Anniversary of Black July: Special Statement by Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said in a statement issued yesterday on the occasion of the 39th anniversary of Black July that we remember those who lost their lives, lost their property and were displaced in the brutal Black July violence against Tamils \u200b\u200bin Sri Lanka.",
        "The massacre of Tamils \u200b\u200bin Colombo followed decades of unrest and tension across the country.",
        "These deadly events, known as Black July, triggered an armed conflict that lasted 26 years. It caused the death of tens of thousands of people. Houses and commercial establishments owned by Tamils \u200b\u200bwere destroyed.",
        "In the months following the Black July violence, the Canadian government implemented a special response to the violence in Sri Lanka. It helped more than 1,800 Tamils \u200b\u200bimmigrate to Canada. I had the privilege of meeting many Tamil Canadians who survived the Black July atrocities.",
        "I was moved by their painful experiences of loss, displacement and regression.",
        "Canada is now home to one of the world's largest diaspora Tamils. We thank Tamil Canadians for contributing so much to making Canada the strong, vibrant and multicultural country it is today.",
        "Canada stands ready to help the people of Sri Lanka affected by the current economic and political crisis. Canada strongly encourages the Government of Sri Lanka and the new President, Ranil Wickremesinghe, recently elected by the Sri Lankan Parliament, to resolve this crisis and undertake the necessary reforms, promote democracy and human rights and uphold the rule of law.",
        "Canada also reiterates the need to ensure that protesters' rights and freedom of the press are protected during these difficult times.",
        "Our thoughts are with all the victims and their families and friends during Black July and the conflict that followed. We are committed to working together to build a better future for all."
      ],
